                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the protagonists; a few lines
                           on the incipit page of Texts IV, V and VII, alternating with black lines;
                           elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals; the word salām or some of its letters; the word hale luya or
                           its abbreviations; a few other words, e.g., sobä (fol. 4v), kämä (fol.
                           6v).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The quality differs throughout the Ms.
                        Possibly several scribes were involved in the copying process. The writing
                        on <locus from="53v" to="57r">53v-57r</locus> is
